What information do you have regarding the following questions on the nature of consciousness: 

1. We have the subjective experience of consciousness, but what are the different ontological viewpoints on how or if it arises? 
2. We know consciousness exists, but what is its purpose, if it has a purpose, according to various ontological opinions?? 
3. According to neuroscience, subjective or phenomenological experience, designated as "qualia," is assumed to be consciousness existing in relation to interactions among neurons in the brain - what is known about the nature of this relationship?
